## 🚫 NEVER DO

1. ❌ Use `print()` - always use `logger`
2. ❌ Raise `HTTPException` in services - use custom exceptions
3. ❌ Put business logic in routes - use services
4. ❌ Use sync SQLAlchemy - always async
5. ❌ Modify old migrations - create new ones
6. ❌ Hardcode credentials - use environment variables
7. ❌ Skip type hints or docstrings
8. ❌ Forget to import models in `db/base.py`
9. ❌ Check roles only in frontend - always verify in backend
10. ❌ Allow users to change their own role
11. ❌ Skip resource ownership checks in service layer
12. ❌ Expose sensitive data to unauthorized roles

